  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks (reserve a few leaves for garnish)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>to a separate pot over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, press down on the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to release the juice – this is your <strong>balsamic tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> to a plate and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Coat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> in the flour, pressing firmly to coat them evenly</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the<strong> coated fish</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, return the potatoes to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of<strong> milk </strong>and the<strong> chopped basil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>basil mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/golden-basa-with-balsamic-tomato-sauce-and-basil-mash/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> golden basa</strong> over the <strong>basil mash</strong> with the <strong>balsamic tomato sauce </strong>drizzled over the top</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>basil leaves</strong></p><p>Season with a crack of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
